{"/service/ndnp/mthi/batch_mthi_douglasfir_ver01/data/sn86075189/00414211057/1958020701/0032.xml":{"full_text":"The Readers' Forum\nApproves PV Stand On\nIndian Termination\nThe People's Voice\nSince some of our members are In\ndian Americans, The Christian Training\nCenter members through the will of\nGod, wishes to protest the move towards\ntermination. To do so would be break\ning the Covenant between the Indians\nand God.\nWe as Christians instead of taking\naway the lands of the Indians, should\nwork towards implementing the treat\nies, especially as regards the Landless\nIndians, that have been terribly cheat\ned. Efforts should be made to rehabili\ntate these good people and prevent the\nheartless discrimination against them.\nWe should ask God to have His way\nthen go forward in a Ohrist-like man\nner. We heed not His command, \"Feed\nMy Flock\".\nOur best wishes to the People's Voice.\nIn The Name of Jesus Christ.\u2014Rev.\nE. A .HERRING, Dean, Christian Train\ning Center, Great Palls.\nMy \"Two-Bit's Worth\nP\nTo those of us who recall the early\ndays of the \"great depression\" it now\nbegins to appear that history is about\nto repeat itself for there are many\npoints of similarity.\nThe \"Great Engineer' (H. Hoover)\nkept repeating that \"prosperity is just\naround the corner\", although no one\nwas able to locate the particular cor\nner. Today President Eisenhower in\nsists that \"the depression (pardon me)\nthe minor recession is only temporary\".\nUnemployment now approaches the four\nmillion mark.\nIn the late twenties unemployment\nreached near five million, bread lines\nwere prevalent, as soup lines become\nmore prevalent today. In the legislative\nsession of '31 I repeatedly warned the\nHouse members that legislative action\nshould be taken to relieve suffering\nand the Montana State Federation of\nLabor called on the Governor (Erick\nson) to call a special session to take\nsome action, just as today the govern\nors of two states (Washington and\nIdaho) have urged a special session to\ncoipe with the problem.\nIn 1931 the International Union of\nthe U.M.W.A. was sending out relief\nchecks to unemployed miners and urg\ning federal action. Today our own\nState Federation President is urging\nthe Governor to seek distribution of\nsurplus foods to the unemployed and\nsimilar actions are being taken in\nother states.\nIn 1931 in response to a resolution\nadopted by the State Federation of\nLabor I sent a series of open letters\nto the Governor (Erickson) citing the\nseriousness of the situation and to\ngether with other similar demands,\nsufficient \"heat\" was appll\u00e8d to cause\nthe Governor to make a \"swing around\nthe state\" to investigate. A series of\n\"hearings\" were held in several locali\nties. In Roundup, the one which I was\nable to attend, many \"free enterprise\"\nbusiness men were present who all\nexpressed the \"hope\" that Musselshell\ncounty had enough \"red-blooded men\"\nto \"take care of her own\", in fact the\ncourtroom, where the hearing was held,\nwas so full of \"hope\" that windows\nand doors had to be opened to let some\nof it out. I then stated to the Governor\nand those present that this problem\nwas just too big for Musselshell, or\nany other county, too big for the Red\nCross and might even become too big\nfor the state and that it was my belief\nthat the federal government would\neventually have to take action.\nEvents of the early thirties indicate\nhow accurate was my prediction. Pres\nent events indicate a great similarity\nto conditions at that time. True the\npresent \"mild recession\" has been cush\nioned to some extent by the \"new\ndeal\" programs then adopted but the\nUnemployment Compensation, the bank\nguarantee law, and \"social security\"\nlegislation are still not adequate to\nprovide the reqired cure should the\n\"mild recession\" continue to grow less\n\"mild\".\nOur State and Federal lawmakers\nwould do well to take a lesson from\npast events and make provision for\nfurther cushioning of such a shock\nelse we may require a still \"Newer\nDeal\" to prevent our present day econ\nomy from going \"entirely bust\".\u2014LE\nVERNE HAMILTON, Thompson Falls\nThe Future Final Phase\nIf my forecast is wrong, there will\nbe nobody in North America to say so.\nA defect of daily newspapers is that\nthey tell nothing of the future; only of\nevents that have already happened.\nAnd those only after we have learned\nabout them on the radio. Even their\neditorials do not tell of coming events.\nAmericans (except those of Irish par\nents) still have the colonial worship\nof England. Men's clothes are made\nafter British fashions. Rhodes' Schol\narships to Oxford are the prime achieve\nments of our bright college students.\nWhen Prime Minister Churchill came\nto Fulton College (never heard of 100\nmiles away) to put cap and gown on\nMr. Truman, and to get a dozen billion\ndollars of our taxes to bolster the posi\ntion of the 'Empire' ias a third strength\npower, it turned our president's head\nto the belief that he knew all about\nworld affairs, and that he was the\nCanute to check the rising tide of\nCommunism in the world.\ncompletely evolved, is\nThere are two political\nSocialism,\nCommunism,\nparties in the world. The Peace Party,\nthe War Party. Roughly speaking, the\nCommunists are of the Peace Party,\nAmerica heads the War Party\u2014yet\nanomalously the Pope speaks for peace.\nHe heads 475 million Catholics. Prob\nably the majority of Americans are\nfor peace. Our Congress does not yet\nknow this. So Jhey are still in the War\nParty, to gain votes.\nAbout scientific matters our Con\nhas been stupid for 168 years.\nenacted the Metric.\npress\nThey have never\nSystem of Weights and Measures. Fin\nally it will dawn on Congress that in\nthe race for scientific achievement our\nchildren are handicapped. Russia of\ncourse is on the Metric System from\ngrade one (as also all South America).\nKerala, a state of India of 20 million\npeople, voted Communist. All India, 350\nmillion people will do likewise. All\nSoutheast Asia is on the way. Formosa\nwill revolt, pitch Chiang into the sea\nand join China. South Korea will join\nNorth Korea, Turkey and the Middle\nEast will go Soscialist. Indonesia, 70\nmillion, is going Communist.\nSouth America will go Socialist. The\nRockefeller Oil in Venezuela will be\nnationalized. Brazil will nationalize\nU. S. holdings. America will go broke.\nBankruptcy is not so bad as war. Demo\ncrats in Washington are worse wastrels\neven than the spendthrift Republicans.\nThe Labor Party will win the next\nelection in Britain. lit will quickly agree\nto the Soviet cry (or demand) for peace\nand disarmament. Every other nation\nin UN will be or go in the Peace Party\nagainst us.\nJust as we followed England in the\nstupid Cold War, we will follow Eng\nTHESE CO-OP ELEVATORS ARE HELPING YOU\nWIN THE BATTLE FOR FAIR FARM PRICES\nPATRONIZE THEM\nI\nGTA LINE ELEVATORS\nBillings\nBozeman\nBroadview\nBrooks\nGarter\nChester\nChinook\nChofeau\nColumbus\nGut Bank\nEthridge\nGildford\nGreat Falls\nHighwood\nHilger\nInverness\nJoplin\nLavin Spur\nLewistown\nMoore\nDevon\nRapelje\nShelby\nSquare Butte\nStanford\nSunburst\nThree Forks\nTiber\nValier\nWinifred\nZurich\nGTA AFFILIATED CO-OPERATIVES\nFarmers Union Elevator Company\u2014Belt\nFarmers Union Elevator Company\u2014Big Sandy\nEquity Co-operative Association\u2014Brady\nEquity Co-operative Association\u2014Conrad\nNorthern Montana Mustard Growers Ass'n.\u2014Conrad\nEquity Co-operative Association\u2014Geraldine\nFarmers Grain Exchange\u2014Havre\nFarmers Union Elevator Company\u2014Ledger\nMolt Farmers Elevator Company\u2014Molt\nFarmers Union Elevator Company\u2014Pendroy\nFarmers Union Elevator Company\u2014Portage\nPower Farmers Elevator Company\u2014Power\nFarmers Union Elevator Company\u2014 Rudyard\nEquity Co-operative Association\u2014Ulm\nFarmers Co-operative Elevator Company\u2014Denton\nDutton Co-operative Association \u2014Dutton\nUnion Elevator Company\u2014Galata\n\n\n\n\nS\n\n1\nif\nFARMERS UNION GRAIN TERMINAL\nASSOCIATION\nI n\nmil\n9\na\ni\nGREAT FALLS, MONTANA\nMar\nkW\n\u25a0(HE CO-OP 1V4y\n\nland In a peaceful negotiation with\n(China and Russia.\nThe \u00ab'\u00ablining generation will look\nhaek on War an we look hack on\nchattel slavery. McArthur says \"War\nis now unthinkable\".\nWest Point will be a Polytechnic\nSchool; Annapolis teach Mercantile\nNavigation\u2014Hydrogen bombs unload\ned, 4-star general uniforms will be\nexhibits in the Smithsonian Institute\nbeside the Flying Machine of Darius\nGreen, that would not fly.\u2014LOWNDES\nMAURY, Butte.\nSTATE OF MONTANA\nLEGAL ADVERTISING\nCertificate of Doing Business\nUnder Fictitious Name\nPursuant to the provisions of Sec\ntion 63-601 through 63-606, Revised\nCodes of Montana, 1947, this is to cer\ntify that the undersigned, FRANCIS E.\nSMALL, an Individual, residing at 317\nSouth Dakota Street, Helena, Montana,\nis doing business under the fictitious\nname and style of PSI CO.\nThat the undersigned's principal\nplace of business is and will be at 317\nSouth Dakota Street, Helena, Montana.\nWITNESS MY HAND AND SEAL this\n15th day of January, 1958.\nFRANCIS E. SMALL\n\nFalkland Islands\nAn arch of whalebones commem\norates the Falkland Islands' entry\ninto the British family of nations.\nThe arch, made from the jawbones\nof two sperm whales overlooks the\nharbor at Stanley, the capital and\nonly town of the island colony in the\nSouth Atlantic.\n:ss\nCounty of Lewis and Clark)\nOn this 15th day of January, 1958,\nbefore me, Gene A. Picotte, a Notary\nPublic for the State of Montana, per\nsonally appeared FRANCIS E. SMALL,\nknown to me to be the person whose\nname is subscribed to the within instru\nment, and acknowledged to me that he\nexecuted the same.\nIN WITNESS WHEREOF, I have\nhereunto set my hand and affixed\nmy Notarial Seal the day and year first\nhereinabove written.\nGENE A. PICOTTE.\nNotary Public for the State\nof Montana. Residing at\nHelena. My Commission ex\npires 1-4-59.\n4T\u20141-17, 24, 31; 2-7.\nWants Utilities To Pay\nFor Their Own Ads\nWASHINGTON, D. C.\u2014(CNS)\n\u2014Congrenman Lester Johnson (D\nWis.) believes utility stockholders\nshould pay for their own propa\nganda.\nTo be iure taxpayer* don't pay\nfor attack* on co-op* and federal\npower dams, Johnson has intro\nduced a bill to keep commercial\nutilities from deducting such ad\ncosts from their pre-tax income.\nHe also wants to protect rate\npayers. Another bill Johnson has\nintroduced would keep the com\npanies from including propaganda\ncosts in any plea for higher rates.\nJohnson want* the companies to\nreport all their propaganda and\npolitical advertising costs to Fed\neral Power Commission and In\nternal Revenue Bureau. The bu\nreau is studying recerit utility ad*\nand may perhaps try to collect more\ntaxes under present law*.","height":"20109","width":"13779"}}
